  "pages": [
    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "An auction of hogs and sheep\nwill be one Of the attractions at\nthe fair grounds on October 8.\nFarmers have been notified of the\nplan, and already several exhibit\nors have agreed to send in stock,\nand it is probable these sales will\nprove satisfactory feature of the\nlivestock show. A number of new\nexhibitors will be present. Among\nthose who have signified their in\ntentions of exhibiting hogs are G.\nw. Clapp of Reardan. w. F. Craw-\nford of Shields, Ore, Ed School of\nAlbany, Ore, Washington Land,\nStock l. Improvement Co. of Cres-\nton, d. P. Wynia of Hillyard, Ha-\nzelwood Co. of Spokane, McCon-\nnell Bros. of Shields, Ore, ]. H.\nSmith of Pullman and Guy Munger\nof Pennington."
    }
  ]
